    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.01195.002_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">The Daily Graphic<ptr target="n0440"/></name>
                    <date when="1874-01-19">January 19, 1874</date>
                </dateline>                
                <salute>Walt Whitman:</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>We enclose the proof of your second article; but would much prefer that you should get the copy 
                <choice><sic>strait</sic><corr>straight</corr></choice> the first time. Such 
                very heavy corrections in proof cause great embarrassment and expense in a newspaper office. We 
                are quite willing to give proofs for verbal corrections; but we do not like to reset and readjust 
                so largely. So please have a care to fix your copy correctly before sending it in.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Yours very truly</salute>
                <signed>DG Croly</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.01195.001_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
